  "body_text": null,
  "page": null,
  "source": "[\\well.ordered{X}]\nStates:\nwhen:\n. X is \\set\nthat:\n. forAll: A is \\set\n  where:\n  . A \\:subset:/ X\n  . not:\n    . A = \\empty.set\n  then:\n  . exists: m is \\set\n    suchThat:\n    . m \\.least.in./ A\nDocumented:\n. called: \"well ordered\"\n. written: \"X? \\text{ is well ordered}\"\n. description: \"A partially ordered set $X$ is well ordered when every nonempty subset of $X$ has a least element. The natural numbers are the prototypical well ordered set.\"\nId: \"5ead27ca-0a76-4340-827c-ac72e5154f35\"",
